The paper deals with the problem of recognizing Wheeler graphs, which are a type of compressed index structure used in string algorithms. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the complexity and inapproximability of various related problems, which suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses techniques from graph theory (cs.CG) and approximation algorithms (cs.GT).
